text.section:
A small employer and the employees of the small employer shall be eligible for a subsidy of small employer health benefit plan premiums if the small employer:
at the time of initial application for the subsidy:
has not offered a small employer health benefit plan to its employees for at least 12 consecutive months;
has at least two but not more than nine eligible employees; and
meets salary and wage requirements established by the Commission;
offers a small employer health benefit plan to its employees;
establishes a payroll deduction plan under § 125 of the Internal Revenue Code;
agrees to offer a wellness benefit, as required by the Commission; and
meets any other requirements established by the Commission.
